# Project rules (OLLAMA workstation)

Full rules: **docs/RULES.md**. Summary:

## Structure
- **docs/** — Documentation and guides (документация и руководства). Hand-written specs, standards, how-tos.
- **docs/reports/** — AI reports only (отчёты ИИ). AI-generated reports and analyses go here.
- **docs/plans/** — Plans (планы). Implementation plans, cleanup plans, roadmaps.
- **code_analysis/** — generated by code_mapper; do not edit. Run code_mapper after file changes.
- Root: docs/, src/, tests/, config/, examples/, .venv, projectid, pyproject.toml.

## Code
- One class per file (except small enums/exceptions). **Max 350–400 lines per file**; split when exceeded.
- Every file header: **Author: Vasiliy Zdanovskiy**, **email: vasilyvz@gmail.com**.
- Imports only at top (except lazy loading). No `pass` in production code; use `NotImplemented` only in abstract methods.

## Checks
- After editing code: run **black**, **flake8**, **mypy** and fix all issues.
- After each batch of changes: run **code_mapper**.

## Environment
- Use project **.venv**; never use `--break-system-packages`.
- Reuse **mcp-proxy-adapter** client/Command/registry; do not duplicate proxy protocol.

## Workstation (OLLAMA tools)
- Tools: OLLAMA format `type: "function"`, `function: { name, description, parameters }` with JSON Schema.
- Mandatory tools: `list_servers`, `call_server`, `help`. Config: `mcp_proxy_url`, `ollama_base_url`, `ollama_model` (required); no hardcoded URLs/credentials.
- On proxy error: put error in tool result content; do not drop conversation. Log without secrets.

## Language
- Documentation: English (unless product owner requests otherwise). Code, comments, docstrings, tests: English only.

## Other
- Commit after logical change; push only on user request. Do not modify files outside the project without permission. Project id in **projectid** file.
